<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>Item&nbsp;1.01</B></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Entry into a Material Definitive Agreement. </B></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">On July&nbsp;20, 2015, Agios
Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (the &#147;Company&#148;) entered into a Second Amendment to the Lease (the &#147;Second Lease Amendment&#148;) with Forest City 88 Sidney Street, LLC (the &#147;Landlord&#148;). The Second Lease Amendment amends certain terms
of the Company&#146;s existing lease with the Landlord, dated September&nbsp;15, 2014 and as amended on November&nbsp;21, 2014 (the &#147;Lease&#148;), pursuant to which the Company leases office space located at 88 Sidney Street, Cambridge,
Massachusetts (the &#147;Premises&#148;). The Second Lease Amendment, which is effective as of July&nbsp;20, 2015, expands the rentable square footage of the Premises from approximately 113,220 square feet to approximately 146,030 square feet.
Pursuant to the Second Lease Amendment, the date on which the Company will become responsible for paying rent with respect to such additional square footage under the Lease is November&nbsp;1, 2015 (the &#147;Expansion Space Rent Commencement
Date&#148;). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Pursuant to the Second Lease Amendment, the Company&#146;s monthly base rent for the Premises will increase from
approximately $549,000 to approximately $727,000 on the Expansion Space Rent Commencement Date, and will increase each year thereafter up to a maximum monthly base rent of approximately $844,000. The Second Lease Amendment also provides for, among
other things, an increase of the Company&#146;s tenant improvement allowance from approximately $16.6 million to approximately $20.5 million and an increase of the Company&#146;s existing security deposit with the Landlord from approximately $2.2
million to approximately $2.9 million. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The foregoing description is a summary of certain terms of the Second Lease Amendment and is
qualified in its entirety by the text of the Second Lease Amendment, a copy of which is filed as exhibit 10.1 to this Current Report on Form 8-K and is incorporated herein by reference. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Form 8-K is incorporated by reference in its entirety into this Item&nbsp;2.03. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>EX-10.1</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="right"><B>Exhibit 10.1 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>SECOND AMENDMENT TO LEASE </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">THIS SECOND AMENDMENT TO LEASE (hereinafter referred to as the &#147;Amendment&#148;) is dated as of this 20th day of July, 2015 by and
between FOREST CITY 88 SIDNEY STREET,&nbsp;LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (&#147;Landlord&#148;) and AGIOS&nbsp;PHARMACEUTICALS, INC., a Delaware corporation (&#147;Tenant&#148;). Capitalized terms used herein and not otherwise defined
shall have the meaning ascribed to such term in the Lease. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">W I T NE S S E T H </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, Landlord and Tenant entered into that certain Lease dated as of September&nbsp;15, 2014 (the &#147;Original Lease&#148;), as amended
by that certain First Amendment to Lease (the &#147;First Amendment&#148;) dated as of November&nbsp;21, 2014 (the Original Lease and First Amendment shall be referred to collectively as, the &#147;Lease&#148;) with respect to certain premises
located at 88 Sidney Street, Cambridge, Massachusetts (the &#147;Premises&#148;); and </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">WHEREAS, Landlord and Tenant desire to amend the
Lease to expand the definition of Premises to include the fifth floor of the Building (the &#147;Fifth Floor Expansion Space&#148;), provide for an additional improvement allowance, and for other purposes, as set forth in this Amendment. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the promises and mutual covenants hereinafter contained and other valuable consideration, the receipt and
sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, Landlord and Tenant hereby agree as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Premises</U>. Effective as of the date hereof, the term &#147;Premises&#148; set forth on Exhibit A of the Lease is deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following: </TD></TR></TABLE>

hereof.&#148; </P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">4.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Annual Increases to Annual Fixed Rent</U>. Effective as of the date hereof, Section&nbsp;3.1 shall be amended by deleting the second paragraph thereof and replacing it with the following: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;On the first anniversary of the Rent Commencement Date, and on each anniversary thereafter, Annual Fixed Rent for Suites 100A, 100, 300
and 400 shall increase to an amount equal to one hundred two percent (102%)&nbsp;of the Annual Fixed Rent immediately preceding such anniversary. On the first anniversary of the Rent Commencement Date, and on each anniversary thereafter, Annual
Fixed Rent for Suites 100B, 150 and 200 shall increase to an amount equal to one hundred three percent (103%)&nbsp;of the Annual Fixed Rent immediately preceding such anniversary. On the first anniversary of the Rent Commencement Date for Fifth
Floor Expansion Space, and on each anniversary thereafter, Annual Fixed Rent for Suite 500 shall increase to an amount equal to one hundred three percent (103%)&nbsp;of the Annual Fixed Rent immediately preceding such anniversary.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">5.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Operating Expenses</U>. Section&nbsp;3.3 of the Lease is hereby amended by adding the following thereto: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;<B>Annual Estimates</B>.&nbsp;Landlord shall deliver to Tenant a written estimate of Operating Expenses for each calendar year during the
Term (the &#147;<B>Annual Estimate</B>&#148;), which may be revised by Landlord no more than twice during such calendar year to reflect actual known or reasonably anticipated increases in Operating Expenses for that calendar year.&nbsp;Landlord
shall use reasonable efforts to deliver the Annual Estimate to Tenant by 60 days prior to the end of each calendar year, and shall take into account any comments by Tenant which are consistent with the rights and obligations of the parties under
this Lease.&nbsp;Landlord shall use good faith efforts to meet with Tenant from time to time prior to November&nbsp;1<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">st</SUP> of each calendar year during the Term upon Tenant&#146;s request to discuss
the Annual Estimate for the upcoming calendar year and Landlord&#146;s budget for Operating Expenses for the Property for such year .&nbsp;The Annual Estimate shall include reasonably detailed line-item costs.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">6.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Tax Protest</U>. Section&nbsp;3.2 of the Lease is hereby amended by adding the following thereto: </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#147;Upon Tenant&#146;s reasonable request, the Landlord shall use reasonable efforts to contest or seek abatement of any Real Estate Taxes
affecting the Premises. Should the Landlord contest or seek abatement of such taxes, then it shall do so with diligence and shall keep the Tenant appropriately informed, in the Landlord&#146;s reasonable discretion, as to such action. Upon
Tenant&#146;s request, Landlord shall provide Tenant with a copy of any notice of the assessed valuation of the Property and/or the Building received by Landlord, as well as copies of all tax bills and tax notices received by Landlord, and copies of
all papers filed by Landlord in connection with any such Tax Protest or Tax Proceeding. Tenant&#146;s rights under this Section may be exercised only in respect of Tax Years occurring subsequent to the Commencement Date.&#148; </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">- 2 - </P>

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">7.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Tenant Personnel</U>. Tenant shall have the right to station its own security or other personnel in the lobby of the Building and upon reasonable advance notice to utilize its own contractors or personnel for
cleaning, maintenance and other similar services in the Building, excluding, however, HVAC or other systems which may be shown as Landlord&#146;s responsibility on the Tenant/Landlord Responsibility Matrix attached as Exhibit H-1. In the event
Tenant utilizes its own personnel or contractors for any such security, cleaning, maintenance or other similar services, Tenant shall pay all costs directly and the same shall not be included in Landlord&#146;s costs for purposes calculating
Operating Expenses for the Property. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">8.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><U>Condition of Fifth Floor Expansion Space/Landlord&#146;s Work</U>. Landlord shall be responsible, at its sole cost and expense, to deliver the base building mechanical systems (HVAC, electrical, life safety and
plumbing), including, without limitation, the hot water heater, and the Shared Laboratory Systems (as defined in Section&nbsp;2.3(c) of the Lease) that service the Fifth Floor Expansion Space in good operating condition and repair, and shall
maintain the same in accordance with Section&nbsp;5.1 of the Lease. Except as provided in this Section&nbsp;7, the parties hereby acknowledge and agree that all work performed by Tenant or required to be performed by Tenant under the Lease has been
performed to the satisfaction of Landlord. Landlord shall remain responsible, at its sole cost and expense, for all work to be performed by Landlord under the Lease (except as otherwise provided in this Second Amendment), including, without
limitation, final completion of all of Landlord&#146;s Work pursuant to Section&nbsp;2.1(c) of the Lease. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
